A woman committed suicide on a highway in Switzerland, and was run over and killed
The victims are lying on the highway during midnight.
This woman who attempted suicide was run over by multiple vehicles on the highway early Thursday morning. The police are looking for witnesses at this time.
The incident occurred in the early Thursday morning at Highway A1 near Morges at the canton of Vaud.
The police of Vaud canton expressed that a woman has, out of “despair”, laid on the highway and was crushed by multiple vehicles.
The victim was a 49-year-old Swiss woman. Her behavior was clearly suicidal. She was run over by multiple vehicles, including a truck.
The woman died on site.
The police expressed that multiple drivers involved in the incident have agreed to become part of the investigation progress, but a number of drivers has yet to confirm the request. The police encourages them and other witnesses of the accident to be part of the investigation.
Lawyer Gilles Hofstetter told Tribune de Genève that criminal investigations have been initiated at this time, a standard procedure for such incidents.
However, he is currently unaware if there are drivers who facing accusations.
Can a collision be avoided?
Hofstetter said, “This will be determined by the prosecutor.”
For two similar incidents that have occurred in the last 5 years, the drivers were not held responsible for this.
According to this report, both cases were caused by people walking on the highway late at night. The final verdict is that the driver cannot predict that there would be pedestrians walking past the highway in midnight.
Last year, a police officer was accused of causing death by negligence. The charge was that in August 2014, she hit a man on the A1 expressway near Payerne resulting in his death.
The court learned that the 22-year old victim walked across the highway after consuming alcohol.
After an investigation, the judge said that the female police officer’s driving behavior was completely legal at the time, and that the appearance of the man on the road was a “totally unexpected and unforeseen circumstance”. What’s more, this female police officer called the emergency services after the incident occurred.
Anyone who can provide information on the incident which occurred near Morges on Thursday should contact the police at 021 644 83 46 or 021 644 44 44.
NASA climate model: Venus used to be hospitable to humans
According to the predictions made by the latest climate model of NASA, Venus was once suitable for human habitation.
Scientists at NASA’s Goddard Space Flight Center developed a model that could explore past conditions of Venus. The tools and algorithms used by this model are very similar to those used by climate scientists.
This model is used to verify whether Venus, with its high surface temperature, lack of water, and an atmosphere filled with carbon dioxide, ever had an earth-like environment.
In the past, scientists thought that the reason for the slower rotation rate of Venus was because it had a thicker atmosphere.
However, the latest simulation indicated that Venus may have had a thinner atmosphere similar to that of Earth, and its rotation speed at the time was similarly slower.
This model can even display the landforms of early Venus.
There may be more dry areas on Venus than on Earth, but it used to have enough water and geographic changes to nurture life as well as to prevent rapid evaporation.
Earlier, the sun was 30% brighter on the surface of Earth than on Venus.
Anthony Del Genio, a scientist in the Goddard Institute for Space Studies explained in a press conference: “In the model simulation used by Goddard Institute for Space Studies, the slow rotation of Venus meant that one side of the planet has a day length of as long as 2 months.”
This makes the surface warm and produces rain that can form thick clouds, which are like an umbrella that blocks most of the heat from the sun.
The results of the simulation show that the average climatic temperature of Venus was actually several degrees lower than that of modern-day Earth.
The evolution of Venus as simulated by this model was similar to earlier estimates made by planetary scientists.
Although life could have existed on Venus, the planet has been exposed to excessively high temperatures and ultra-violet rays over the course of billions of years.
The ocean on the planet evaporated, and the water vapor was also burnt away by UV radiation.
As hydrogen escapes, what remains are the thicker CO2 atmosphere and lethal greenhouse gas effect, forming what we now know as Venus.
Researchers published new results of Venus weather simulation models on the journal of Geophysical Research Letters
Patrick Roy resigned from his position as the captain of the Colorado Avalanche.
Patrick Roy resigned from his position as head coach and vice-president of the Colorado Avalanche, and expressed that he had no voice in decision making for the team.
Colorado’s Executive Vice President & General Manager Joe Sakic confirmed the news, and said that the club will immediately start looking for a new coach.
50-year old Roy expressed in a statement: “For the last 3 years, I have been actively, passionately, and doggedly live up to my duties as the head coach and vice president of the Colorado Avalanche.”
I have been thinking seriously all summer how to improve this team so that they can become stronger.
In this regard, the objective of the head coach and the Vice President must be consistent with that of the club.
He must be given a voice when making decisions that impact team performance.
However, these conditions have yet to be met.
Sakic hired Roy on May 23, 2013, and thanked Roy for the contribution he made to the team.
Sarquiss said, “Patrick informed me of his decision today.”
I thank them for his contributions for the club and wish him success in the future.
Roy was nominated as the League’s best coach in the Jack Adams Award in the first season after becoming the avalanche coach in 2013-2014.
He helped the club score 112 points, allowing them to secure the top rank in the central region. However, the Colorado team was defeated and ousted by the Minnesotans in the first round of the post-season games, and continued to miss post-season games in the two most recent years.
During the 2015-2016 season, the performance of the Avalanche include 39 victories, 39 draws, and 4 defeats. The team lost the second wild card qualification short of 5 points for the Western Hockey League.
As the goalkeeper of the hall of fame, Roy has won 4 Stanley Cups, winning two of them while playing for the Montreal Canadiens and another two while playing for Avalanche.
North Sea oil field workers end strike, negotiations continue
The chief negotiations representative expressed that the North Sea Oil workers have stopped strikes regarding employee pay. Both parties have initiated a new round of negotiations for this dispute.
The North Sea oil platform operated by the Royal Dutch Shell has experienced multiple strikes directed against the oil field service company Wood Group.
According to a joint statement, “Wood Group, Unite, and RMT unions can verify that we have agreed to restart the process to address the current dispute.”
We will start earlier from next week onward. In the next few weeks, multiple full-day conferences will be held. These issues will be re-examined.
